<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:22PM EDT  by NWS Binghamton</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Luzerne
County through 245 PM EDT...
At 222 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stoddartsville, or 12 miles southeast of Wilkes-Barre, moving
northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Stoddartsville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
